	<key>readme</key>
	<string>## Prompteria Alfred Workflow

Search and copy prompts from your Prompteria library.

### Usage

**Search:** Type `prompts` to search, then ↩ to copy via Prompteria (app shows template var dialog if needed).

**Add:** Type `add-prompt` to add clipboard content as a new prompt (prompts for title, description, folder; uses Inbox if no folder specified).

### Requirements

- [Prompteria](https://github.com/fortin/prompteria) app installed with prompts created
- Alfred 5 with Powerpack

### After import

- Set category to **Productivity**: right-click workflow → Category → Productivity

### Using the installed app

By default the workflow uses the app in `/Applications` (opened by bundle ID `com.prompteria.app`). Ensure Prompteria is installed there.

To use the Xcode build instead: create `prompteria_app_path.txt` in the workflow folder with the path to your `Prompteria.app` (e.g. `~/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData/.../Build/Products/Debug/Prompteria.app`). Remove that file to switch back to the installed app.</string>
